        Advance your career at Liberty Mutual - A Fortune 100 Company!
        As a Analyst/Senior Analyst on the Claims Advanced Analytics team (within U.S. Consumer Markets), you will take the lead on understanding Claims business strategies, goals, and processes to identify the opportunities to deploy predictive/prescriptive analytics, as well as work through the practical application within a complex environment. U.S. Consumer Markets has put strategic importance and excitement around modeling in Claims. You will focus on building and presenting the business case to Claims Senior/Executive Managers where one or more models can optimize calls / claims channeling, reduce loss cost, increase staff productivity, or improve customer experience across various Claims lines of business (LOB's). Once support is gained, you will be responsible for designing, executing, and monitoring a pilot to gather operational and analytical insights, and determine if there is value for a countrywide implementation. There is also the opportunity to learn to build simple linear and explanatory models from data scientists on the team. You will also support these data scientists in manual scoring of data for some deployed complex models. This dynamic role provides broad exposure to all Claims functions, offering a unique view into the operations, proposed improvements, strategic initiatives, and other new developments underway.
